---
layout: default
title: "Is Book Too Long For You? Read a Little Book"
id: "little-books"

inspiration:
    - https://youtu.be/1HBNrwapfv0?t=1269: "Specialized micro-sites over general-posts-group"
---

{block content}
    <div class="container">
        <h1>{$title}</h1>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-12">
                <p>
                {=date('Y')} is the fastest year ever. More and more information and too little time to read books. <strong>We need clear, short, cohesive, updated and social content</strong>. A year old book has much less value then post from today, moreover in programming.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <div class="col-4 pull-right">
                       <img src="https://kayiprihtim.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/kucuk-yayinevleri-ust.jpg" class="img-thumbnail">
                    </div>

                    Once, I was writing a book. But I realized that by the end of the writing it would be outdated, so I could start rewriting right away. Still, some <strong>topics deserve more then 3 posts in a book style</strong>.
                </p>
                <p>I looked for something in <strong>between a post and a book</strong>...</p>
                <br>
                <p>
                    <em>A Little Book</em>
                </p>
                <br>
                <p>
                    â†“
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <hr>

        {foreach $little_books as $little_book}
            <h2 id="{$little_book['title']|webalize}">{$little_book['title']}</h2>

            {var $totalReadingTime = 0}
            {foreach $little_book['post_ids'] as $postId}
                {php $totalReadingTime += $posts[$postId]->getReadingTimeInMinutes()}
            {/foreach}

            <ul class="list-inline post-metadata">
                <li class="list-inline-item mr-3">
                    <em class="fa fa-calendar fa-fw"></em> {$little_book['year_released']}
                </li>
                <li class="list-inline-item mr-3">
                    <em class="fa fa-clock-o fa-fw"></em> {$totalReadingTime} mins
                </li>
                <li class="list-inline-item mr-3">
                    <a href="#{$little_book['title']|webalize}">#Anchor</a>
                </li>
            </ul>

            <ul class="mt-4">
                {foreach $little_book['post_ids'] as $postId}
                    {var $activePost = $posts[$postId]}
                    <li class="mb-3">
                        <a href="/{$activePost['relativeUrl']}/">{$activePost['title']|noescape}</a>

                        {include "postMetadataLine", post => $activePost}
                    </li>
                {/foreach}
            </ul>

            {sep}<hr>{/sep}
        {/foreach}
    </div>

    <br>
    <br>
    <br>
    <br>
{/block}
